      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Hemolysis index (HI) absolute level comparison",
      "description": "Predicted normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) values compared to in-vitro measurements from a standardised bovine blood loop at 37 °C. Inherent biological variability across blood donors was assessed qualitatively by the experimental team and noted in the test report as 'moderate'; no structured probabilistic UQ node was constructed for this result because the variability was characterised through expert elicitation rather than a formal Monte Carlo or interval-analysis workflow. The absence of a machine-readable UQ link for this result constitutes the targeted weakness W-AL-01.",
