    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the package based on the overall weight of evidence from 13 credibility factors, acknowledging that achieved levels fall below required levels for several factors. The Monte Carlo UQ coverage across velocity, pressure, and wall shear stress validation results was judged sufficient for submission. The hemolysis index validation result (VR-03) characterised biological variability qualitatively; the team noted this as a documentation gap but did not elevate it to a formal weakener, creating the targeted W-AL-01 condition whereby aleatory uncertainty for the primary QoI remains uncharacterised in structured form.",
